Episodes.Title: Joey Fatone's Dance Party
Episodes.Actors: James Murray, Brian Quinn, Sal Vulcano
Episodes.Plot: The Jokers are bad receptionists and must do and say what the other guys tell them. Then it's a Joker vs Joker challenge with Joey Fatone, followed by an epic punishment culminated by the Joker's previous punishments.

Episodes.Title: Tournament of Losers
Episodes.Actors: James Murray, Brian Quinn, Sal Vulcano
Episodes.Plot: Uh oh. Kicking good people out and stealing from strangers is what's on the agenda for the Jokers this week, with one of them ruining the entire night of a whole sports bar in tonight's big punishment.

Episodes.Title: Servin' Up Laughs
Episodes.Actors: James Murray, Brian Quinn, Sal Vulcano
Episodes.Plot: The Jokers spend time reviewing Bonus Clips from Season 10 that have never been seen before. The Jokers are served the clips by Cole, their supervising producer, posing as a waiter with comedic timing.

Episodes.Title: Let It Roll
Episodes.Actors: James Murray, Brian Quinn, Sal Vulcano
Episodes.Plot: Stealing America's hearts isn't the only thing on the agenda, because the Jokers will also be stealing America's babies at the mall. While they lie in wait trying to succeed in an impossible task, they'll hash on never-before-seen...

Episodes.Title: Personal Be-Wrongings
Episodes.Actors: James Murray, Brian Quinn, Sal Vulcano
Episodes.Plot: No sudden movements. The Jokers are hiding from their boss, then (trying) to get away with sending bizarre emails. But ultimately, one loser won't make it through, and is caught red handed messing with women's purses.
